MILWAUKEE AMERICAN ASSOCIATION v. K. M. LANDIS et al. No. 4586. Circuit Court of Appeals, Seventh Circuit. Dec. 31, 1931. G. M. Peters, of Chicago, Ill., for appellant. Leslie M. O’Connor, of Chicago, Ill., for appellee.

Before ALSCHULER, EVANS, and SPARKS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

On motion of counsel for appellants, it is now here ordered, adjudged, and decreed, by this court that this appeal be, and the same is hereby, dismissed, with costs.
